hero text;Hi Quality Silencers | OEM Specification Silencer Manufacturer & Professional DPF Cleaning Experts


🚛 Hi Quality Silencers

Professional DPF | DOC | SCR | ASC Cleaning

📘 Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ)

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

❓1. Why should a DPF be cleaned?

When soot and ash accumulate inside the DPF and cause blockage:

⚠️ Engine performance may decrease.
⚠️ Fuel consumption may increase.
⚠️ The risk of turbocharger damage may increase.
⚠️ Components such as the EGR Valve, Differential Pressure Sensor, and EGT Sensor may be affected.
⚠️ The engine may overheat.
⚠️ The DPF Warning Light or Check Engine Light may illuminate.
⚠️ Emission control efficiency may decrease, resulting in increased pollution.
⚠️ In severe cases, DPF replacement may become necessary.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

❓2. When should DPF | DOC | SCR | ASC be cleaned?

The emission system should be inspected if you notice any of the following symptoms:

✅ DPF Warning Light is ON.
✅ Reduced vehicle performance.
✅ Loss of pulling power.
✅ Excessive black smoke from the exhaust.
✅ Abnormally high exhaust temperature.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

❓3. What should be done first if these symptoms appear?

✅ First, have the vehicle inspected at an authorized service center.

• Perform a Forced Regeneration.
• If the blockage is caused only by light soot accumulation, the issue may be resolved through regeneration.

❌ If the warning light remains ON or back pressure is still high, professional cleaning is required.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

❓4. What should the vehicle owner do before professional cleaning?

At an authorized service center:

✅ Using an OBD diagnostic scanner, record the following values:

• Soot Value
• Clogging Percentage
• Fault Codes

These records help verify the effectiveness of the cleaning by comparing the values before and after the service.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

❓5. What is Professional DPF Cleaning?

Professional DPF Cleaning is a scientific and safe process that removes soot, ash, oil residue, and other contaminants accumulated inside the DPF honeycomb channels.

It is not just a simple water wash or heat treatment.

Our professional cleaning process consists of four stages:

1️⃣ Chemical Soaking

The DPF is immersed in a specially formulated cleaning solution to soften accumulated soot, ash, and oil residues.

2️⃣ Hydro-Pneumatic Cleaning

Using water and compressed air, contaminants are safely removed from the honeycomb channels by cleaning in both flow directions.

3️⃣ Thermal Regeneration

Carbon deposits are burned off under controlled temperatures without causing damage to the DPF.

4️⃣ Final Pressure Test

Back pressure and airflow are tested to ensure the DPF has been cleaned effectively and is ready for reuse.

✅ Key Benefits of Professional Cleaning

• Restores proper airflow.
• Reduces back pressure.
• Improves engine performance.
• Helps improve fuel efficiency.
• Extends the service life of the DPF.
• Reduces the likelihood of future blockages.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

❓6. What happens if only heat treatment or pressure washing is performed?

⚠️ Ash cannot be completely removed.

As a result:

• The DPF may become blocked again.
• Engine performance may decrease.
• The warning light may reappear.
• The risk of DPF damage may increase.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

❓7. Why does the warning light remain ON even after DPF cleaning?

This may be due to one or more of the following reasons:

✔️ A Diagnostic Trouble Code (DTC) is still stored in the ECU.
➡️ Scan and clear the fault codes using an OBD diagnostic scanner.

✔️ The DPF Ash Counter or Soot Load has not been reset.
➡️ Perform a DPF Reset, Ash Counter Reset, or Learned Values Reset.

✔️ Forced Regeneration is still required.
➡️ Perform Forced Regeneration using a diagnostic scanner.

✔️ A problem with the Differential Pressure Sensor or Pressure Pipes.
➡️ Inspect the sensor and hoses, and clean or replace them if necessary.

✔️ Faulty Exhaust Gas Temperature (EGT) Sensor.
➡️ Check live data and perform sensor diagnostics.

✔️ The DPF has not been cleaned completely.
➡️ Perform a Differential Pressure Test or Flow Test to verify airflow.

✔️ Other engine-related faults (Injector, Turbocharger, EGR Valve, Intake Leak, etc.).
➡️ These engine faults should be repaired first.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

❓8. How long does professional cleaning take?

⏳ Typically 1–2 working days.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

❓9. How much does DPF cleaning cost?

💰 DPF cleaning starts from ₹6,000.

(The final cost may vary depending on the vehicle model, DPF size, and overall condition.)

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

❓10. Should the DPF unit be removed before cleaning?

✅ Yes.

The DPF unit must be removed from the vehicle before professional cleaning.

📦 DPF units can be sent to us by courier or parcel from anywhere in India.

After cleaning, the unit is tested thoroughly and returned ready for installation and use.
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

